Description: Fragment of handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Kleitomachos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0161.12. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 206, 2.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0848)
